{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "Define one or more package traits to offer default and configurable features for a package.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/PackageManagerDocs\/documentation\/PackageManagerDocs",
        "doc:\/\/PackageManagerDocs\/documentation\/PackageManagerDocs\/AddingDependencies"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/PackageManagerDocs\/documentation\/PackageManagerDocs\/PackageTraits"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Swift Package Manager"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Providing configurable packages using traits"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swift packages before version 6.1 offer a non-configurable API surface for each version.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Starting with Swift 6.1, packages may offer traits, which express a configurable API surface for a package.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use traits to enable additional API beyond the core API of the package.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "For example, a trait may enable an experimental API, optional extended functionality that requires additional dependencies, or functionality you may want to enable only in specific circumstances.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Traits that you specify when building a package only activate within the package you’re building.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "If your package wants to use a trait in a dependent package, it needs to encode the traits it needs in its dependencies.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Don’t remove or disable public API when you enable a trait.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Within the package that defines a trait, the trait expresses conditional compilation.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Swift Package Manager exposes enabled traits as conditional blocks (for example, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "#if YourTrait",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") that you can use to conditionally enable imports or different compilation paths in code.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Trait names are namespaced within the package that hosts them.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "A trait name in one package has no impact on any other package.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Trait names must be ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swift-book\/documentation\/the-swift-programming-language\/lexicalstructure#Identifiers",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " with the addition of the characters of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "-",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "+",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Don’t use the trait names ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "default",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "defaults",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " (regardless of capitalization).",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "These values aren’t allowed to avoid confusion with the default traits that a package defines.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Declare-traits",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Declare traits",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Create a trait to define additional functionality, and define it in the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swiftpm\/documentation\/packagedescription\/package\/traits",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " property of the package manifest.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Use ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swiftpm\/documentation\/packagedescription\/trait\/default(enabledtraits:)",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to provide the set of traits that the package uses by default.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "If you don’t define a default set of traits to enable, Swift Package Manager enables no traits by default.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The following example illustrates a single trait, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "FeatureA",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", that is enabled by default:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ ...",
            "traits: [",
            "    .trait(name: \"FeatureA\"),",
            "    .default(enabledTraits: [\"FeatureA\"]),",
            "],",
            "\/\/ ..."
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Traits can also represent a set of other traits, which allows you to group features together.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The following example illustrates defining three traits, and an additional trait (",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "B-and-C",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") that enables both traits ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "FeatureB",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "FeatureC",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ ...",
            "traits: [",
            "    .trait(name: \"FeatureA\"),",
            "    .trait(name: \"FeatureB\"),",
            "    .trait(name: \"FeatureC\"),",
            "    .trait(name: \"B-and-C\", enabledTraits: [\"FeatureB\", \"FeatureC\"]),",
            "    .default(enabledTraits: [\"FeatureA\"]),",
            "],",
            "\/\/ ..."
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For the example above, the default trait is ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "FeatureA",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Changing the default set of traits for your package is a major semantic version change if it removes API surface.",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "Adding traits isn’t a major version change.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swift Package Manager treats traits as purely additive, and unifies enabled traits across all packages within the build graph.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Design your traits so that they enable additional API (and their dependencies, if needed).",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Define-mutually-exclusive-traits",
          "level" : 4,
          "text" : "Define mutually exclusive traits",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The package manifest format doesn’t support declaring mutually exclusive traits.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "In the rare case that you need to offer mutually exclusive traits, protect that scenario in code:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "#if FeatureA && FeatureC",
            "#error(\"FeatureA and FeatureC are mutually exclusive\")",
            "#endif \/\/ FeatureA && FeatureC"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Providing mutually exclusive traits can result in compilation errors when a developer enables them.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Depend-on-a-package-with-a-trait",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Depend on a package with a trait",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A package dependency that doesn’t specify traits uses the package with its default traits enabled.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "To enable specific traits, add them to the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "traits",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " parameter in the package dependency declaration.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The following example shows how to depend on ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swift-configuration",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " with both the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "defaults",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "YAML",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " traits enabled:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "dependencies: [",
            "    .package(",
            "        url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-configuration.git\",",
            "        from: \"1.0.0\",",
            "        traits: [",
            "            .defaults,",
            "            \"YAML\"",
            "        ]",
            "    ),",
            "]"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "When you specify traits for a dependency, you explicitly define which traits to enable.",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "The default traits aren’t included automatically.",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "To use both the default and additional traits, add ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : ".defaults",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " to the list of traits you specify.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Tip",
          "style" : "tip",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Use-traits-in-your-code",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Use traits in your code",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use the name of a trait for conditional compilation.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Wrap the additional API surface for that trait within a conditional compilation block.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "For example, if the trait ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "FeatureA",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is defined and enabled, the compiler sees and compiles the function ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "additionalAPI()",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "#if FeatureA",
            "public func additionalAPI() {",
            "  \/\/ ...",
            "}",
            "#endif \/\/ FeatureA"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Use-a-trait-to-enable-conditional-dependencies",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Use a trait to enable conditional dependencies",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "You can use a trait to optionally include a dependency, or a dependency with specific traits enabled, to support the functionality you expose with a trait.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "To do so, add the dependency you need to the manifest’s ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "dependencies",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " declaration,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "then use a conditional dependency for a trait or traits defined in the package to add that dependency to a target.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The following example illustrates the relevant portions of a package manifest that defines a trait ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "FeatureB",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", a local dependency that is used only when the trait is enabled:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ ...",
            "traits: [",
            "    \"FeatureB\"",
            "    \/\/ this trait exists only within *this* package",
            "],",
            "dependencies: [",
            "    .package( ",
            "        path: \"..\/some\/local\/path\",",
            "        traits: [\"DependencyFeatureTrait\"] ",
            "    \/\/ this enables the trait DependencyFeatureTrait on ",
            "    \/\/ the local dependency at ..\/some\/local\/path.",
            "    )",
            "]",
            "\/\/ ... ",
            "targets: [",
            "    .target(",
            "        name: \"MyTarget\",",
            "        dependencies: [",
            "            .product(",
            "                name: \"MyAPI\",",
            "                package: \"MyDependency\",",
            "                condition: .when(traits: [\"FeatureB\"]) ",
            "    \/\/ if the FeatureB trait is enabled in *this* package, then",
            "    \/\/ the `MyAPI` product is included as a dependency for `MyTarget`.",
            "            )",
            "        ]",
            "    ),",
            "]"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The following code wraps the import with the trait’s conditional compilation, and defines additional API that uses the dependency:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "#if FeatureB",
            "    import MyAPI",
            "#endif \/\/ FeatureB",
            "",
            "\/\/ ...",
            "",
            "#if FeatureB",
            "    public func additionalAPI() {",
            "        MyAPI.provideExtraFunctionality()",
            "        \/\/ ...",
            "    }",
            "#endif \/\/ FeatureB"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
